transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Thank you for calling. This is John. How can I help you?

Speaker 2: Yes, I'm calling in reference to the new pill, ADV.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: I'm in the system. I just updated the card and everything.

Speaker 1: Now, what was the promotion I got for the Gender Promotion thing I have for the pills?

Speaker 2: I need your name and zip code real quick, sir.

Speaker 1: Okay. Name is Kelvin, K-E-L-V-I-N.

Speaker 2: And last name Wilkes, W-I-L-K-E-S.

Speaker 1: Okay. And the zip?

Speaker 2: 11422.

Speaker 1: Thank you. One second. I'm pulling up your account.

Speaker 2: Okay. 133rd Ave. in Rosedale?

Speaker 1: That's correct.

Speaker 2: Okay. So the last time you ordered, you got five pills at $63.95.

Speaker 1: We've actually changed the plan, so you can get ten for that same price.

Speaker 2: We do have more than ten if you want to get that, but if you're looking to pay something similar, we can get you ten.

Speaker 1: Ten is good.

Speaker 2: Ten is good? Okay.

Speaker 1: You updated the card, so...

Speaker 2: The Discover card is the one you want me to use, right?

Speaker 1: That's right. 0373.

Speaker 2: It did update properly, so I'll go ahead and charge that card for you.

Speaker 1: That's what I needed.

Speaker 2: All right. You're getting ten of the AGV, sir.

Speaker 1: These should ship out on Monday for you.

Speaker 2: Appreciate you. Thank you.

Speaker 1: Good luck with the storm that's coming through.

Speaker 2: Me, I just finished having a throat cut, but I won't be doing none of that.

Speaker 1: I'm in the house for six months.

Speaker 2: Oh, well...

Speaker 1: I got you.

Speaker 2: Even if it was going to snow you in any way, it doesn't matter.

Speaker 1: Well, I hope you recover well, sir, and you'll get these in about a week or so.

Speaker 2: Yes. Appreciate you. Thank you.

Speaker 1: Of course. Bye-bye.
